<HEADLINE> Iran, Ethiopia Calls for Promotion of Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi and his Ethiopian counterpart Seyoun Mesfin here on
Wednesday urged to prepare a suitable ground for upgrading mutual
cooperation and accelerating implementation of agreements.
</P>
<P>
In their first round of talks, the two ministers discussed
bilateral ties, expansion of trade and economic cooperation,
regional developments and cooperation at regional and international
levels, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Stating that Africa has special status in Iran's foreign
policy, Kharrazi called for building up efforts to identify each
other's potential and adopting practical steps to increase mutual
transactions and the economic and commercial relations.
</P>
<P>
He voiced Iran's readiness to contribute to development of
Ethiopia and said that Iran-Ethiopia joint economic commission
session was a step towards identification of potentials,
organization of activities and implementation of projects.
</P>
<P>
Mesfin said that his country is interested in making use
of Iran's experiences and expanding political, economic and
cultural relations with the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran and Ethiopia enjoy necessary potential to
enhance their role in south-south cooperation and various
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian official, who arrived here Wednesday morning,
also invited Kharrazi to pay an official visit to Ethiopia.
</P>
</TEXT>
