<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Studies Maize Production Cost </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 2 (Xinhua) --Zambia has started a cost study of
maize, the staple crop of the African country, in a bid to boost
its agricultural competitiveness in the region.
</P>
<P>
With favorable climate and soil for maize production, Zambia
failed to compete favorably with that from neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest magazine of the Zambia Farmer, the
study, sponsored by the Zambia National Farmers Union, would
search for the cause of the poor efficiency of maize production
and compare its costs with that of other countries in the region
and North and South Americas.
</P>
<P>
The study will impact significantly on the livestock, poultry
and dairy sectors and also benefit coffee, cotton, wheat, soya and
tobacco productions in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
