<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Forces Re-capture Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government forces
announced that they have recaptured Cuima, a city 73 kilometers
south of Huambo, a major city in central Angola, after they
recaptured several other cities recently.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Sunday, the government said that the
government forces killed over 10 military men of the National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA), captured
another three, and seized a lot of weapons in the battle over the
city.
</P>
<P>
The government forces drove UNITA military out of Tchicala
Tcholoanga City, about 50 kilometers west of Huambo last week, and
then on Saturday re- claimed Tchidinji, a city about 100
kilometers west of Huambo, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The government forces also destroyed one of UNITA's military
bases about 60 kilometers east of Huambo, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The government forces have since mid-May launched large scale
offensive against the UNITA, with fighting mainly concentrated on
central Angola's Huambo and Kuito cities, after the government
announced never to open peace talks with UNITA again.  
</P>
</TEXT>
