<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Launch Survey on Family Income, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Central Statistical
Authority of Ethiopia said here Wednesday that a two-phase survey
on family income, consumption and expenditures will start from
selected residential councils of capital Addis Ababa over the
coming two months.
</P>
<P>
Samiya Zekeria, deputy general manager of the authority, said
that the survey is to be conducted on over 26,000 sample families
across the nation.
</P>
<P>
It will focus on the background and personal status of family
members, their weekly consumption of, among others, food and drink
as well as their overall income, the Ethiopian News Agency quoted
Zekeria as saying.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the survey will help identify the basic
problems affecting the living standards of the people in the
metropolis.
</P>
<P>
She called on capital residents to give full cooperation to the
data collectors, saying that data collectors would repeatedly call
on target families in the course of the survey.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier announcement by the authority, the
first phase of the survey will be conducted in June and July this
year, while the second phase would be carried out in December this
year and January next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
