National Authority (PNA) expects the new Israeli government to
announce its policy regarding the expansion of Jewish settlements
initiated by the outgoing Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
PNA Minister of Local Government Saeb Erekat said the PNA hopes
Israeli prime minister-elect Ehud Barak and his new cabinet to
take a clear stand on the settlement issue to re-activate the
peace process. (BC-Palestine-Israel-Settlement)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- One was killed and another injured on Wednesday in an
aircraft crash in central Iran, the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
A training aircraft crashed at 10:00 hours local times (0530
GMT) near the village of Meshkan in Kashan region, Isfahan
province, the report said. (BC-Iran-Crash-Aircraft)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Three Iraqi civilians were injured on Wednesday in
the U.S. and British bombardment of civilian facilities and
military camps, an Iraqi military spokesman announced.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that at 11:00 (0700 GMT), 11 formations of
enemy warplanes coming from Turkish airspace violated northern
Iraqi airspace over the provinces of Dohuk, Neineva and Erbil.
(BC-Iraq-US Attack) 
</P>
