<HEADLINE> French President Meets with Cambodian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac met
with visiting Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen at the Elysee
presidential palace on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen explained to Chirac the three ``axis'' of domestic
policy, which are national reconciliation and political stability,
strategy of integrating Cambodia into the international community,
economic and social development with international aid, according
to Elysee press service.
</P>
<P>
The French president expressed his support to this policy and
said that France will support the measures to be taken by the
Cambodian government to revive the country, devastated by nearly
three decades of war.
</P>
<P>
Chirac called on Cambodia to conclude an agreement with the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) on economic readjustment, which
he said will increase the confidence of the international
community in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
He also said that France condemns the genocide perpetuated by
the Khmer Rouge regime in the 1970s and wishes that those held
responsible for the genocide should be punished by the law.
</P>
<P>
Chirac and Hun Sen also discussed bilateral cooperations in
clearing up land mines, training medical personnel, constructing
an airport in Phnom Penh, training engineers and high level
technicians, fighting against AIDS and protecting Cambodia's
cultural treasure Angkor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
