<HEADLINE> (EDS: Updates With More Details) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were killed
and some 80 others injured as an American Airlines flight with 145
people aboard skidded off a rain-slicken runway, broke apart and
burst into flames in Arkansas State of the United States before
midnight Tuesday, reports reaching here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Flight 1420, a Super MD-80, had 139 passengers and six crew
members and was due to arrive in Little Rock National Airport at
9:41 p.m.( local time). The flight from Dallas of Texas State was
delayed for more than two hours and arrived just as the storm was
hitting Little Rock, capital of Arkansas State, with lightning,
hail and winds gusting to nearly 90 mph ( 145 kph).
</P>
<P>
Passengers described a scene of terror, with the twin-engine
jetliner splitting into pieces and catching fire after it slid to
the edge of the Arkansas River. Some passengers squeezed one by
one through an emergency exit as flames spread through the plane.
</P>
<P>
The deaths are the first in an U.S. commercial airline accident
since December 28, 1997, when a woman was killed aboard a United
Airlines 747 that encountered severe turbulence over the Pacific.
</P>
<P>
After sliding down the runway, the twin-engine Super MD-80
slammed into a steel tower, split into pieces, caught fire and
wound up on the edge of the Arkansas River.
</P>
<P>
As flames spread through the plane, some passengers squeezed
one by one through an emergency exit while others escaped through
openings created when the plane's fuselage fractured. They
scrambled away from the plane across lowlands near the river in
darkness, rain and hail.
</P>
<P>
"We grabbed each other and ran away," said Missy Lewis,
traveling with her husband and teen-age daughter.
</P>
<P>
Sources familiar with the investigation said authorities could
account for nine deaths in the crash of Flight 1420. The airline
said the plane's captain was among those who died. 
</P>
</TEXT>
