<HEADLINE> Truck Carrying Explosives Overturns in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A tractor-trailer loaded with 20
tons of explosive firework powder overturned at a major highway
interchange in Fairfax County of Virginia State in the United
States early Wednesday, prompting the evacuation of dozens of
homes and clogging rush-hour traffic in the Washington area.
</P>
<P>
The flatbed truck ran off a ramp at the interchange of I-495,
I-395 and I-95, the major north-south highway linking New York and
Florida States. Traffic was backed up for dozens of kilometers,
including the outer loop of the beltway surrounding the nation's
capital.
</P>
<P>
Local firefighters created a 700-meter safety zone around the
site. More than 50 homes and 150 people were evacuated as a
precaution.
</P>
<P>
The explosive powder, the type used to make fireworks, was
inside a cargo container atop a flatbed trailer. None of the
powder spilled from its container.
</P>
<P>
Neither the driver nor her boy friend were injured in the
accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
