<HEADLINE> Sierra Leone Tops List of African Refugee-Producing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone is at the top
of the list of refugees-producing countries on that continent with
410,000, according to an African Fact Sheet issued Wednesday by
the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees(UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
Somalia is the second with a little over 400,000, Sudan
follows with more than 370,000, Eritrea with over 340,000 and
Burundi with nearly 300,000.
</P>
<P>
Countries hosting the biggest numbers of refugees are Guinea
with more than 410,000, Sudan with more than 390,000, Tanzania
with more than 340,000 and Ethiopia with more than 260,000.
</P>
<P>
These refugees are among 3.3 million in Africa, which is
also home to some 2.1 million internally displaced and 1.1
million former refugees who have recently returned home,
according to UNHCR.  
</P>
