<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Air Force helicopter on a
training mission crashed in a wooded area at Fort Bragg in North
Carolina State of the United States on Wednesday night, killing
one person and injuring five others, reports reaching here said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Military Officials said there did not know what caused the MH-
53J Pave Low aircraft to go down.
</P>
<P>
