percent in April as consumers rushed to lock in low mortgage rates.
The rise follows a 0.8 percent decline in March. Meanwhile, Car
sales rose to record or near-record levels for many auto makers in
May. Ford and Daimler-Chrysler had gains, but GM's sales dropped
5 percent, partly from weak Chevrolet sales. 
