<HEADLINE> Euro-Mediterranean Symposium on Renewable Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The European-Mediterranean Symposium
on Power Efficiency and Renewable Energy opened here Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The event has attracted experts from 30 countries and is being
attended by Secretary-General of the World Solar Committee as well
as representatives of the European Commission and the United
Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
The three-day symposium will deal with issues related to the
renewable energy and the challenges facing the Euro-Mediterranean
region in this area, the Tunisian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It will also discuss the economization of energy and the
technicalities of the renewable energy in industry, rural
development and water desalination.
</P>
<P>
In her inauguration address, Tunisian Minister of Environment
and Territorial Management Faiza al-Kafi urged the public and
private institutions of coastal countries of the Mediterranean Sea
to seek possible investment and partnerships to develop clean and
renewable energy particularly the solar energy.
</P>
<P>
On the fringe of this event, Faiza inaugurated the Renewable
Energy Exposition that attracted 55 manufacturers from 30
Mediterranean countries. The exposition exhibits the latest
technologies in the field of renewable energy related to industry,
construction, water pumping, home consumption and the introduction
of renewable energy usage in the rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
