<HEADLINE> U.S. Warplanes Bombard Northern Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S. warplanes Thursday bombarded
military control facilities in the south of Mosoul city in
the no-flying zone in northern Iraq, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a statement issued by the U.S. Air Base in
Incirlik, southern Turkey, said that the U.S. F-16 and F-15
fighter jets threw CBU-10 and CBU-12 type bombs on the targets.
</P>
<P>
The statement added that all the fighter jets had returned to
the base after participating in the operation in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of the American warplanes are stationed at the Incirlik
military base to launch attacks on the targets in northern Iraq.
