<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Almost No Ecological Changes in Three Gorges Area, Surveys Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's State Environmental
Protection Administration (SEPA) said today that the general
ecology in the Three Gorges Project area basically remained the
same last year as the year before.
</P>
<P>
It also called for urgent measures to protect wild animals and
forests in the area.
</P>
<P>
The SEPA said in an annual environmental monitoring bulletin
released today that the people moved out of the reservoir area
have remained healthy, and the undertakings concerning science,
education, culture and social security in the region have
witnessed a rapid development.
</P>
<P>
The environment has been improved and plant species have
remained quite rich, it said, adding that the water quality of the
mainstream of the Yangtze River has remained good, with no
remarkable changes during the year.
</P>
<P>
However, the bulletin points out that the top priority must be
to protect local wild animals and forests, and to get rid of the
garbage along the river.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Ecological and Environmental Monitoring System,
set up in 1996 by government departments in charge of
environmental protection, agriculture and forestry, has enabled
scientists to collect a lot of data and played a major role in
coordinated development of environmental improvement and
construction in the area.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin, based on the data, is released every year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990603.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Monarch Feared Killed in Nigeria's Regional Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Monarch of an Itsekiri community was
feared killed Wednesday by Ijaw militant youths in the deepening
crisis, which has claimed more than 200 lives, in southern
Nigeria's port city of Warri.
</P>
<P>
Olara-Aja of Ugborodo, the monarch of an Itsekiri community in
the Warri South West Local Government Area, was missing and
allegedly beheaded by some youths suspected to be Ijaws, reported
Punch, a major Nigerian daily Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The alleged king came after reports of a fresh Itsekiri
counter-attack on Ijaw communities, leading to the death of seven
persons.
</P>
<P>
The Itsekiris allegedly launched the attack on Sahara Bubon, an
Ijaw community, at about 6:30 p.m. (1730GMT) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian government Tuesday had urgently deployed an additional
150 soldiers to the troubled Warri area in the country's oil rich
Delta Sate as conflict there seemed to be escalating.
</P>
<P>
Delta State Governor James Ibori had also held an urgent
meeting with leaders of Ijaw, Itsekiri, and Urhobo, the three
main ethnic groups in Warri region Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Militant Ijaw youths Monday touched the entire Itsekiri
dominant village of Aruton, including two primary and one
secondary schools, killing reportedly about 200 people.
</P>
<P>
Although Delta governor pledged his support for the agitation
by the youths for better stake in the national resources located
in their communities, he condemned the use of violence.
</P>
<P>
The trouble was triggered when tax collectors from the two
council areas, which are in a hot debate over the ownership of
the area, are on their revenue drives one week ago.
</P>
<P>
Warri area is traditionally a headache for the state as well as
the federal government for the local ethnic communities are on
constant fighting against each other and the government on
division of land and oil benefit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
