<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 12:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clashes Erupt Between Palestinians and Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- "No peace with settlement" is no mere
a slogan carried by the Palestinians today, better known as the
"day of anger, in the face of Israeli settlers, but is a true
event unfolding in Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Violent confrontations raged out in the day between angry
Palestinian youths, on the one hand, and Israeli troops, on the
other, opposite the settlement of Nitsareem in the Khan Younis
governorate, south of Gaza.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged stones for tear gas grenades and rubber
bullets. At least two injured Palestinians were rushed to hospital.
</P>
<P>
At the crossroads opposite the settlement of Kosh Karif located
in the vicinity of the Khan Younis municipality, about 1,000
Palestinians from all walks of life staged peaceful marches in
protest against Israeli settlement activities in Palestinian lands.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli troops in charge of protecting the settlement were
on a high alert. Thereupon, the Palestinian police force
intervened to separate the masses and the Israeli troops.
Demonstrations and speeches went on in a quiet, peaceful
atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The masses, expressing their outrage, shouted slogans such as
"no peace with settlement", "settlements an international crime",
"no to settlements - no to Judaization of Jerusalem - yes to
checking occupation out of Palestinian lands".
</P>
<P>
In a statement to Xinhua, Dr Awad Higazi, chairman of the
national and Islamic anti-settlement committee in the southern
zone, said these marches are an expression of the Palestinian
people's determination to defend their lands, and constitute a
clear message to the Israeli government to learn that settlements
will not find stability.
</P>
<P>
"Though peace is our strategic option. But, he who seeks
settlement does not really want peace, because peace and
settlement will never meet, " he added.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Ibrahim Abul Naja, speaker of the Palestinian
Legislative Council, told Xinhua, "should the Israeli government
fail to put an end to settlement practices which aim at seizing
and usurping our territory, the Palestinian people are not
responsible for whatever takes place later.
</P>
<P>
Ibrahim held the world responsible for confronting the Israeli
government which disregarded agreements signed with the
Palestinian side.
</P>
<P>
He said the Palestinian people were asserting their basic
principle of "no peace with settlement and no negotiations with
settlement".
</P>
<P>
Ibrahim demanded the Israeli government to cease all settlement
activities and to abolish all that had taken place.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sakhr Bassisso, governor of the Khan Younis
governorate, told Xinhua that "the Palestinian people are for
peace, but the peace process is presently facing the dangers of
settlement activities."
</P>
<P>
"We want peace, but on the basis of restoration of Palestinian
people's rights, hence, the prevalence of security and stability
in the region, " he said.
</P>
<P>
"We want Israel, once our enemey, to become a partner in the
institution of peace in this region," the governor added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, anti-settlement mass movements have taken place on
Thursday throughout the West Bank in response to a resolution
adopted by the fifth anti-settlement national conference of May
30.
</P>
<P>
The conference designated today as the "day of anger and
rejection" of Israeli settlement practices in Palestinian lands.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, Palestinian in Jerusalem went on general strike in
the day in solidarity with the national events taking place in the
West Bank and Gaza.
</P>
<P>
The number of Israeli settlements on Palestinian lands has run
up to 170 units with a population of well over 200,000 people by
the end of 1998, according to the Israeli Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
