<HEADLINE> Tibetan Ruling on Mineral Resources Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Tibet's regulation on mineral
resources will go into effect July 1, a local official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The code will encourage farmers and herdsman to develop mines
to promote economic development, the official source said.
</P>
<P>
The regulation stipulates that those who develop mines shall be
responsible for protecting resources and ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
The Tibet Autonomous Region is rich in mineral resources and
geologists have found 99 different minerals there, and 30,
including chrome, boron, and gold, with relatively large reserves.
</P>
