<HEADLINE> Southeastern Chinese Province Increasing Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's coastal province of Fujian
is finding more effective ways to control industrial pollution and
promote development.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the provincial Environmental
Protection Bureau today, total emission of pollutants last year
was as significantly controlled as planned and the amount of
environmental spending as a part of provincial GDP last year was 1.
25 percent, higher than for the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection departments in the province have
established a hotline so that people can quickly phone in
environmental rule violations.
</P>
<P>
Last year the province dealt with some 800 environmental rule
violations and more than 4,100 complaint letters from the public.
</P>
<P>
It also found that 93.9 percent of its construction projects
passed environmental department inspections. 
</P>
