<HEADLINE> Japan Scores Goaless Draw with Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Japan failed to delight its home fans
as the hosts played a goalless draw with Belgium in the three-
nation Kirin Cup soccer tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"It was very good 0-0 draw and means we kept our chances alive,
" said French coach Philippe Troussier, "we will wait until Sunday
to decide who will be the winners."
</P>
<P>
The Japanese were a bit tense in the first half, but made no
mistakes as the Belgians pressed very hard for a victory although
Sandy Martens, Marc Hendrikx and Gert Verheyen all missed their
shots.
</P>
<P>
Verheyen was close to the goal as his shot hit the left post
soon before the break.
</P>
<P>
The home side also had its chance when substitute Atsushi
Yanagisawa produced a pass for Wagner Lopes in the 76th minute,
who netted in but was ruled off side.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes later, Mbo Mpenza also netted an off-side goal
after a corner.
</P>
<P>
"Normally, we have to win a game of this level. I believe we
must have scored two goals in the first half. Japan also must have
scored one goal," said Belgian head coach Georges Leekens.
</P>
<P>
Belgium ended with two draws after they held Peru 1-1 in the
opener last weekend. They were to leave for South Korea Friday
morning for a friendly match.
</P>
<P>
Peru will take on Japan on Sunday to vie for the 160,000 US
dollars title. 
