<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Expects Bumper Crop: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh is expecting a bumper
harvest this year, with the total food cereals production to reach
over 21 million tons, a 5-percent increase over that of last year,
Agriculture and Food Minister Begum Motia Chowdhury said here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We have made a conservative estimate on the basis of available
data up to May 1999, that the food cereals production this year
would surely be a total of 21.358 million tons," she told a press
conference.
</P>
<P>
The government's war-footing efforts to produce more food in
the country had amply contributed towards this year's bumper crop
production, she pointed out.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this bumper crop, she said, "We have constantly
maintained a coordination in the distribution of fertilizer and
other agri-inputs as well as supplying diesel with the help of the
concerned ministry for irrigation purpose to the crop areas
throughout the country."
</P>
<P>
Crop damaged by flood and bumper crop following a flood "was
never a miraculous event" in this country, she said, explaining
that since flood-silt enhances fertility of land, crop production
automatically increases but there must be sincere efforts of the
government.
</P>
<P>
The total food cereals production this year would register an
increase by one million tons over last year's level despite the
century's worst flood that created havoc on the overall economy
and the agriculture in particular, she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
