<HEADLINE> Bomb Explodes in Central New Delhi, Injuring Over 25 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 25 people, including
three policemen, were injured here Thursday afternoon when a bomb
exploded outside a police post in central New Delhi.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims, who were rushed to various hospitals in
the capital, had suffered splinter injuries and the condition of
one of them was said to be serious.
</P>
<P>
The bomb, kept in a bag, was found abandoned in a popular sweet
shop and was handed over by a shop employee to a sub-inspector of
the police at the police post, according to a police officer.
</P>
<P>
The bomb, which was kept outside the police post, exploded at
around 14:55 local time even the police were informed about the
bomb disposal, said deputy commissioner of the police in charge of
north Delhi M. S. Upadhye.
</P>
<P>
The explosion extensively damaged the police post besides six
vehicles including three cars and a police patrol motorcycle.
</P>
