<HEADLINE> Chinese City to Build Big Bell for Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The city government of Wuhan in
central China announced today it plans to build a 21-ton bronze
bell by the end of this year to mark the forthcoming millennium,
at the request of local residents.
</P>
<P>
The bell, to be known as the Wuhan Millennium Lucky Bell, will
be placed in the Yellow Crane Pavilion Scenic Zone, a well-known
tourism area in the city, the capital of central China's Hubei
Province.
