<HEADLINE> China Steps Up Management of Fund for Water Conservancy Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Finance and
Ministry of Water Resources today jointly issued guidelines to
enhance the management and guarantee the rational and effective
use of the funds earmarked for the basic construction of water
conservancy facilities.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, the basic task of the management is
to raise, appropriate and use the funds and to lower the
construction costs and improve investment efficiency.
</P>
<P>
It urges departments of finance and water resources at all
levels to strengthen supervision over uses of the funds and the
processes of project construction, and to make timely corrections
when problems occur.
</P>
<P>
The budgetary fund for the construction must be used
exclusively and is not permitted to be used for other purposes.
Those who violate the stipulations will be punished, the document
says. 
