<HEADLINE> China Shows Military Auto Vehicle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese military cross-field
truck that has won a national prize for scientific advancement was
put on public display for the first time at the Auto Parts,
Manufacturing and Related Products Show (AMS '99) held in Beijing
this week.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River brand heavy duty truck is widely used in
China's armed forces and can be converted to carry strategic
missiles.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle incorporates a unique independent suspension system
that China developed and incorporates the engine and driver's
chamber from the Steyr-Daimler-Puch company of Germany.
</P>
<P>
An officer of the Second Artillery Forces of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) of China said at the show that the vehicle
has the best performance among its rivals in the country. He said
that the new version of the vehicle features enhanced comfort and
reliability as it has adapted German parts and components.
</P>
<P>
He said that China needs to accelerate development of its own
military vehicles so as to avoid dependence on overseas products.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle was developed by the China National Heavy-Duty
Truck Corporation (CNHTC). An official of CNHTC said that the
company has already developed a more advanced model than the one
displayed at the show. 
</P>
