<DOCNO> XIE19990603.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwandan C. Bank Officials held over Money Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Twenty Central Bank officials have
been arrested over the loss of 30 millions Rwandan Francs (RF) or
87,714 U.S. dollars since the end of last week ; official sources
from the Rwandan Central Bank disclosed.
</P>
<P>
"The money displaced ranged between 20 million RFs (57,142
dollars) and 30 million RFs (87,714 dollars) only made up of 5,000
notes which were designed to be "recycled for the new ones," the
Rwanda News Agency (RNA) quoted official sources from the Bank as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The detainees deny misplacing all that much. However, they
agree to have distributed among themselves 10 million RFs (28,571
dollars) which they say will be disbursed .Official sources say
the money was locked up in its fullness.
</P>
<P>
It is said that outdated money is kept in safe custody and is
only opened if all officials are available.
</P>
<P>
Those who were arrested include those responsible for recycling
and the supervisors. However, they do not accept the
accountability of the rest of the money other than 10 million RFs
(28,571 dollars) they shared among themselves.
</P>
<P>
Further investigations are being undertaken by the Central Bank
Governor Francois Mutemberezi and the criminal Investigation
Department in Kigali.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank , following a presidential decree no. 03/01 of
March 17, 1999, is to introduce new Rwandan currencies of 5000,
1000 and 500 notes to ease the misplacement . 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
