<HEADLINE> Filippines Urged Not to Detain Chinese Fishing Vessels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"This act was in violation of the most basic humanitarian
principles, as they used a warship to ram an unarmed Chinese
fishing vessel," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"It is known to everyone that Huangyan Island is part of
Chinese territory and the area where the incident occurred is
within the Chinese fishermen's traditional fishing area," he added.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years the Philippino side has time and
again detained Chinese fishing vessels and fishermen in the south
China Sea, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that China has already expressed its strong
displeasure at the actions of the Filipino navy, and urged the
Philippine side to punish those responsible for the incident and
compensate the Chinese fishermen for their losses. 
