<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Beats Guatemala in Canada Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Canada scored two goals against nil
to beat Guatemala as Jason Devos netted in one and set up the
other in the Canada Cup tournament in Edmonton on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This was the second win for Canada in four days over the
Central Americans.
</P>
<P>
In another game, Iran played a 1-1 draw against Ecuador as
substitute Ali Mousavi scored in the 65th minute for Iran, a
repeat of the only other soccer game between the two countries 27
years ago in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Alberto Morano opened the account with a header in the 39th
minute from a corner kick before Mousavi levelled the scoreboard
after Ecuadorean goalkeeper Jose Cevallos slipped off the ball.
</P>
<P>
The Wednesday's doubleheader only attracted a crowd of 5,821 at
the 61,000-capacity Commonwealth Stadium.
</P>
<P>
While Brazil and Costa Rica pulled out, Ecuador has its full
team in its preparation for the Copa America soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
Iran is the only team that made to last summer's World Cup.
Canada and Guatemala are fielding young teams that feature members
of their under-23 Olympic squads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
