<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket closed
higher Thursday on surging blue-chip industrial stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index finished 26.9 points firmer
at 2,941.6.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials climbed 52.7 points or 1.02 percent to
5,195.2 while the resources index managed only a 4.0-point rise to
1,133.6.
</P>
<P>
Among the resources, Australia's biggest company BHP rose a
modest 5.3 cents to 16.21 Australian dollars, global miner Rio
Tinto slipped 13.6 cents to 22.594 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index eased 1.8 points to 839.0 as the price of bullion
was trading in Sydney 2.10 U.S. dollars softer at 263.90 U.S.
dollars per fine ounce.
</P>
<P>
The banks were mixed, with the industry index adding 15.8 points
to 6,705.4.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank closed 25 cents dearer at 26.00
Australian dollars, ANZ bank rose 7.5 cents to 11.325 Australian
dollars, the Commonwealth Bank of Australia lost 11 cents at 25.17
Australian dollars and Westpac Bank ended eight cents weaker at
10.29 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 415.55 million shares traded worth
704 million U.S. dollar. Rises outpaced falls by 645 to 566 with
449 stocks steady.  
</P>
</TEXT>
