<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Gain 0.10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks overcame sharp
session losses and edged up 12.97 points, or 0.10 percent, to
close at 12,471.61 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Finance and Properties lost 0.12 percent and 0.39 percent
respectively, while Utilities and Commerce &AMP; Industry gained 0.70
percent and 0.29 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index fell 0.94 percent and the
Hang Seng China-affiliated Corporations Index went down 0.43
percent.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's turnover amounted to 5.025 billion HK dollars (644
million U.S. dollars), 980 million HK dollars (125 million U.S.
dollars) less than Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index moved down 44.32 points, or 0.36
percent, to open at 12,414.32 Thursday morning, and went sharply
lower at lunch break mainly on fears of U.S. interest rates. The
share prices rebounded in cautious trade but remained weak
throughout the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
