<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's 1st District Councils Election to be Held on Nov. 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) has decided to
hold SAR's first District Councils election on November 28, 1999,
which is a Sunday.
</P>
<P>
An SAR government spokesman said Thursday that nomination of
candidates for the election will commence in October and a series
of publicity activities will be launched by the government from
August to November to promote the coming District Councils
election.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also said that the District Councils (Election
Petition) Rules have been made by the Chief Justice of the Court
of Final Appeal.
</P>
<P>
The Election Petition Rules provide for the regulation of
matters relating to the preparation, lodgment, service, trial,
withdrawal and costs of any such election petitions.
</P>
<P>
A total of 390 District Council members will be returned by the
election in November 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
