<HEADLINE> China's Position Persistent on June 4 Incident: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's conclusion on the June 4
incident in 1989 is correct and its position on the incident is
persistent, and it will by no means be changed, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
It was "very necessary" for the government to take timely and
resolute steps to maintain China's stability, Zhu stressed.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told a regular press conference that few western media have
waged an anti-China propaganda campaign in the excuse of the 10th
anniversary of the June 4 incident.
</P>
<P>
"This is no news but politics played up by them, and it is very
unpopular," Zhu added.  
