<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Concerted Efforts Called for Better Future for Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- On the occasion of the 200-day
countdown to Macao's return to the motherland, the leaders of
several social organizations in Macao called on local residents to
make concerted efforts to create a promising future for Macao.
</P>
<P>
Ng Si Meng, director of the Macao Association of Neighborhood
Communities, said that the association is holding activities to
enhance the residents' enthusiastic expectations for Macao's
return.
</P>
<P>
"Through these activities, we want them to have a sense of
urgency about the returning process, and arouse their confidence
in the notion of Macao people governing Macao," Ng said.
</P>
<P>
Local people all pin high hopes on the chief executive of the
future Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) and expect that
he will be able to usher Macao into a novel era, Ng Si Meng said.
</P>
<P>
"In the meantime, I wish that the Macao people can take an
active part in the work related to the return and exert joint
efforts to build a beautiful future," he said.
</P>
<P>
Pun Hun Veng, director of the Macao Association of Trade Unions,
said that he feels rather excited because Macao is going to be
reunited with the motherland in 200 days.
</P>
<P>
"The date of December 20 indicates the end of foreign rule in
Macao," he noted. "Moreover, it signifies the formal
implementation of the principles of 'one country, two systems,'
'Macao people governing Macao' and a high degree of autonomy in
Macao," Pun said.
</P>
<P>
The period of 200 days toward Macao's return is critical since
it is a period for the chief executive designate to organize the
SAR government and make preparations for the transfer of power,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Pun added that the residents, especially workers in various
social sectors, should take part in Macao's development with an
attitude of being masters of their own affairs.
</P>
<P>
Kun Sai Hoi, director of the Macao Association of Civil
Servants, said that the association will actively advocate the
awareness of historic mission among civil servants, so as to
enable them to contribute to Macao's steady transition and a
smooth transfer of power.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official report, the localization of
civil servants is not well done. However, most of the localized
civil servants are diligent and devoted to their duty, Kun Sai Hoi
said.
</P>
<P>
"Being a vital force to execute the policies of the government,
civil servants will do their best in the process of organizing the
SAR government," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
