<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Holds Talks with DPRK Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, held talks with Kim
Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's
Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) at
the Great Hall of the People here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who leads the first high-level DPRK delegation to China in
the past five years, is expected to exchange views with Li Peng on
bilateral ties and issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
At press time, the talks are still going on.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here believe that the first high-level
mission to China since President King Il Sung passed away in 1994
marks the restoration of traditional exchanges of high-level
visits between the two countries after a lapse of five-year
suspension. 
</P>
