<HEADLINE> International Anti-Drug Meeting Vows to Build Drug-Free World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The 10th Anti-Drug Liaison Officials'
Meeting for International Cooperation (ADLOMICO) ended here
Thursday afternoon with a declaration to fight for a drug-free
world.
</P>
<P>
More than 120 experts and officials from Interpol, the United
Nations Drug Control Program and 18 countries attended the two-day
meeting and passed a "Seoul Declaration on Policy Directions
toward a Drug-Free World."
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, participating nations reaffirmed their
determination to fight against illicit drugs and fulfill their
obligations to bequeath future generations a healthy, drug-free
society that ensures human dignity and stability.
</P>
<P>
In the declaration, the ADLOMICO appealed for closer
cooperation at the national, regional and international levels
under the principle of common and shared responsibility for the
entire international community.
</P>
<P>
"We call upon each government to establish and implement a
balanced and comprehensive 'National Drug Control Strategy,' which
includes both supply control and demand reduction measures, and to
provide adequate financial and human resources for effective drug
strategies," said the declaration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
