<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Buy Ukrainian Tanks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus is believed to be in talks
with Ukraine to buy up to 40 T-84 MBT tanks, the Cyprus Mail
newspaper reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the Cypriot government is holding
talks with the Ukrainian Kharkov Morozov Design Bureau and its
associated production company, the Malyshev plant, for the
acquisition of the battle tanks.
</P>
<P>
These tanks would complement 45 Russian T-80 tanks bought by
Cyprus in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Each T-84 is priced at 2.2 million U.S. dollars. The Ukranians
can promise the delivery of 10 to 12 tanks within four to six
months.
</P>
<P>
The T-84 tank is based on the T-80 UD design but has a
different turret.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus currently has 27 T-80Us and 14 T-80UDs. 
