<HEADLINE> 20 Percent Zambian Population Infected HIV/AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A report from Zambian Central
Statistics Office has revealed that 20 percent of the Zambian
population is HIV/AIDS infected.
</P>
<P>
The report available here Thursday said the most affected areas
in the country are along the line of rail and the urban areas.
</P>
<P>
"Twenty-five percent of these are from the urban while 13
percent are from the rural areas," the report said.
</P>
<P>
It attributed the high number of cases along the line of rail
to the influx of truck drivers.
</P>
<P>
A joint United Nations program on HIV/AIDS report states that
13.9 million people have died of AIDS worldwide since the epidemic
started in 1979.
</P>
<P>
The report said 3.2 million children aged between 10-15 years
have died of the epidemic of which the sub-Saharan region had
recorded the highest number. 
</P>
