<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Southern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A quake measuring 4.5 degrees on the
Richter scale on Thursday morning jolted Iran's southern Far
province, the Islamic Repubic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The tremor occurred at 8:20 a.m. local time (0350 GMT) and its
epicenter was 50 kilometers south of Shiraz, the provincial
capital, according to the seismological base of the Geophysics
Institution affiliated to Tehran University.
</P>
<P>
So far no report is available about any possible casualties or
damages.
</P>
<P>
Two powerful earthquakes measuring 6.8 and 5.9 degrees rocked
the region on May 7, killing 28 people and injuring more than 100
others.
</P>
<P>
Since then, hundreds of aftershocks and over 10 earthquakes
measuring over four degrees have been registered.
</P>
<P>
Geologists predicted that strong and mild aftershocks will
continue to hit the area until September. 
</P>
