<HEADLINE> No Change To Overseas Investment Policy: Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- China's policy on overseas
investment will remain unchanged whatever the circumstances, the
Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi Guangsheng
stressed while visiting two joint ventures here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"China will remain firm on the policy of reform and opening up
and its policy of absorbing overseas investment in an active and
effective manner will remain unchanged," he said while inspecting
the production lines of the Beijing Ericsson Mobile Communications
Co. Ltd. "The only changes, should they occur, will be policy
improvements."
</P>
<P>
The minister and Beijing Deputy Mayor Zhang Mao also inspected
the Beijing Nokia Mobile Telecommunications Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Antti Ware, general manager of Beijing Nokia Mobile
Telecommunications LTD., told Shi that since production began in
1996, Beijing Nokia achieved one billion yuan (about 120.48
million US dollars) sales volume in its first year. The sales
volume reached 6.2 billion yuan (about 746.99 million US dollars)
last year.
</P>
<P>
The company's exports hit 80 million US dollars in 1997 and 170
million US dollars in 1998. Exports between January and April this
year were also "quite good."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Robert J. Parris, managing director of the Beijing
Ericsson Mobile Telecommunications Co. Ltd., said that Ericsson's
sales income hit 3.4 billion yuan (about 410 million US dollars)
in China in 1998, which made China Ericsson's biggest market
worldwide.
</P>
