<HEADLINE> China Preparing Against Typhoons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua)-- China is making preparations against
typhoons, which are set to come in the July-September period, said
China Daily today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Zhou Wenzhi, vice-minister of Water
Resources, as saying that 27-29 typhoons are to appear this year
in the Pacific, with seven to nine reaching China.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 12 typhoons appeared in Northwest Pacific Ocean and
South China Sea, the lowest figure since 1949. Only three of them
reached China's coast.
</P>
<P>
The coastal Jiangsu Province is now upgrading early warning
systems and telecommunications networks and wave breakers.
</P>
<P>
Another coastal province, Zhejiang, is investing 2.8 billion
yuan (337 million US dollars) in building wave control facilities.
</P>
