<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 2 (Xinhua) -- George Foreman, a 50-year-old
former heavyweight champion, hopes to fight against Mike Tyson in
a bout that would pay Tyson $25 million and Foreman $20 million.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Showtime network, which shows Tyson's fights,
said they were interested and Tyson adviser Shelly Finkel did not
discount the possibility of a matchup between the two former
champions.
</P>
<P>
