<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dagang Wildcatters Strike Black Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese wildcatters recently
achieved a daily output of 144 cu.m. of high quality crude oil and
612,000 cu.m. of natural gas at a wildcat well in Tianjin's Dagang
Oil Field.
</P>
<P>
The production verified expert predictions that the oil-bearing
strata contains abundant reserves and portended bright prospects
for the future of the Dagang Oil Field.
</P>
<P>
The wildcaters discovered the oil-bearing strata earlier this
year near Qianmiqiao while drilling another well nearby.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that total gas and oil reserves in the oil
bearing strata will equal as much as 130 million tons of crude oil.
</P>
<P>
The Dagang Oil Field covers 18,000 sq.km. on the west coast of
Bohai Bay some 50 km from Tianjin. Dagang is the most important
energy base for the major port city in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
A total of 800 million tons of oil reserves and 35 billion cu.m.
of gas reserves have been verified since 1964.
</P>
<P>
The field has estimated total oil and gas reserves of well over
350 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
