<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hold Trade Fair in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will hold a trade fair in
Bangkok, Thailand, from August 12 to 15, aimed at stimulating
trade between the two countries, official newspaper The New Light
of Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar Trade Fair '99, sponsored by the country's
Cooperative Department and the TTF Co. of Thailand, is to take
place in exchange for the first Thai Trade Exhibition held in
Yangon last December.
</P>
<P>
The two sponsoring organizations are inviting local Myanmar
private entrepreneurs to take part in the fair and display their
products.
</P>
<P>
The first Thai trade exhibition in Myanmar was sponsored by the
Department of Export Promotion of the Thai Ministry of Commerce in
collaboration with its Myanmar counterpart under the Myanmar-Thai
economic cooperation promotion program.
</P>
<P>
The TTF Co. of Thailand has also sponsored a number of
exhibitions in Myanmar since 1997, including Yangon International
Trade Fair, First Yangon Gems Fair and the First and Second
Housing and Building Exhibitions.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, bilateral trade including
border trade stood at 441.97 million U.S. dollars in 1998, up from
282.85 million dollars in 1997. 
</P>
