<HEADLINE> Argentina Promotes Trade With Asia-Pacific </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Argentine government has
been applying a strategy of trade promotion with the Asia-Pacific
region, an official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a lecture organized here by the Entrepreneurial and Social
Sciences University, Foreign Ministry official Eduardo Sadous said
the trade volume between Argentina and the Asia-Pacific region had
almost tripled from 2.082 million U.S. dollars in 1991 to 6.166
million dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Asia-Pacific region will always be a
particularly attractive market for Argentina because of the fast
growth of the market, the abundance of business opportunities and
the complementarity of the foreign trade structures between
Argentina and the region.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that economic relations between Argentina and
the Asia-Pacific countries remained weak in trade and foreign
direct investments, pointing out that this region only accounts
for less than 8.5 percent of Argentina's exports.
</P>
<P>
With the revival of Asian economies after the crisis, he said
he is optimistic about future trade between Argentina and the Asia-
Pacific region. 
