<HEADLINE> DPRK High-Level Delegation Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A high-level delegation of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) led by Kim Yong Nam,
president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly,
arrived here this morning for a five-day official goodwill visit
to China, at the invitation of the Standing Committee of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
This is the first high-level exchange between the two countries
since the passing away of President Kim Il Sung five years ago.
</P>
<P>
