<HEADLINE> Indonesia Hopes Its Bridge Team Can Win Bermuda Bowl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Indonesian
Contract Bridge Association (Gabbsi) Wiranto is hopeful that
national players will continue a run of winning form to triumph in
the Bermuda Bowl World Championships and Venice Cup in January
next year.
</P>
<P>
"I believe our team, especially the men's team, can win in the
Bermuda Bowl because they eliminated other strong teams in the
just concluded Asia Pacific Bridge Tournament," Wiranto said.
</P>
<P>
"The men's team defeated New Zealand and Australian teams from
zone VII and China from zone VI. It's not an exaggeration to hope
they win the Bermuda Bowl. We finished second in the 1996 Bridge
Olympics in Rhodes, Greece, after losing to France," Wiranto was
quoted by The Jakarta Post Thursday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia men's and women's teams won the 39th Asia Pacific
Bridge Tournaments in Guangzhou, China, last week. Both teams also
won tickets to the World Championships in Bermuda.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto was satisfied with both the men's and women's teams
results in qualifying for the World Championships.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time we have managed to have both the men's
and women's team qualify for the championships," he said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia last won the Asia Pacific trophy in 1993. 
