<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Tap U.S. Tourism Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will soon launch an
extensive promotional tourism drive to tap the tourist market in
the United States, the state press reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As a prelude to the drive, authorities are planning to appoint
a Sri Lankan honorary director of tourism in New York to handle
the promotional activities, the Daily News said.
</P>
<P>
"Our tourism industry will receive an unprecedented boost if we
could capture even a small percentage of this market," said W.P.S.
Jayawardena, secretary of the Tourism Ministry.
</P>
<P>
U.S. tourists are considered to be high spenders and prefer
destinations which are eco-friendly and of historical
significance.
</P>
<P>
A recent promotional tour of officials to the United States led
by Minister of Tourism Dharmasiri Senanayake was a great success
which enabled the groundwork to be laid for the drive.
</P>
<P>
A large number of American tourists visit India and other Asian
countries regularly. It is expected that Sri Lanka could also draw
a portion of this tourist traffic.
</P>
<P>
More than 381,000 tourists came to Sri Lanka last year, an
increase of 4 percent over 1997. The most arrivals were from West
Europe and Asia. 
</P>
