<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Rice Exports Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Thai rice exports in the first five
months of this year earned 691 million U.S. dollars, down by 22
percent from 885 million dollars a year earlier, according to the
Foreign Trade Department of the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the volume of rice exported also declined to 2.31
million tons from 2.81 million tons.
</P>
<P>
However, prospects were improving in terms of volume for the
rest of the year, Pracha Charutrakulchai, the department's
director-general, was quoted Thursday by the Bangkok Post as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Exports for May increased by about 10 percent year-on-year to
472,000 tons from 427,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
But the shipments were worth 121 million dollars, down from 140
million dollars a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Even so, May's figure was an improvement from 370,000 tons
exported in April, 450,000 tons in March, 430,000 tons in February
and 560,000 tons in January.
</P>
<P>
Export figures would be boosted by the government's sale of
300,000 tons of rice to Iran, pending shipment of 200,000 tons to
Indonesia and a deal with the Philippines, Pracha said.
</P>
<P>
China would also buy 200,000 tons this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I believe Thai rice exports on a government-to-government
basis will pass 500,000 tons projected earlier," Pracha said.
</P>
<P>
Export approvals were currently for an average of 20,000 tons a
day, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
