<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
Wednesday closed with the benchmark IPC index down 36.22 points or
0.67 percent, to 5,400.2 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 70.761 million shares for an amount of
around 110.268 million U.S. dollars, against 67.016 million shares
worth 112.661 million dollars on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.95 to one dollar for
sale and 9.60 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, maintaining the same rate of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the peso fell for the eighth time in nine days as
rising U.S. interest rates lured investors from Mexican securities,
cutting demand for pesos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
