<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States Dominate Chemnitz Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The American sprinters dominated the
athletics meet at Chemnitz, Germany, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
American sprinters swept the 100-meter dashes. Dennis Mitchell
won the men's 100 meters with a time of 10.17 seconds. The women's
100 meters title went to Zundra Feagin who won in 11.55.
</P>
<P>
Derek Mills, also from the United States, won the men's 400
meters at 45.44.
</P>
<P>
Veteran German long jump star Heike Drechsler and her teammate
Susen Tiedtke were beaten in the women's long jump.
</P>
<P>
Dawn Burrell took first place with a leap of 6.76 meters. Olga
Rublyova of Russia finished second at 6.62. Drechsler managed
only 6.54 and Tiedtke's best was 6.53. 
</P>
</TEXT>
