<HEADLINE> Bulgarian MiG-21 Crashes, Both Pilots Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A Bulgarian Air Force MiG-21 crashed
near the village of Dragomir in the Plovdiv region (South Central
Bulgaria) Wednesday, killing both pilots, the Defense Ministry
announced.
</P>
<P>
The pilots, identified as Captain Georgi Roussev and Senior
Lieutenant Sasho Nikolov, died when their plane crashed during a
training mission at noon.
</P>
<P>
A military commission has been appointed with Major General
Ivan Parapounov as its head to investigate the accident.
</P>
<P>
President Peter Stoyanov, Defense Minister Georgi Ananiev and
Chief of General Staff Colonel General Miho Mihov have offered
condolences to the bereaved families. 
</P>
