<HEADLINE> China Lose First Match in Handball World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China lost their first preliminary
match in Group D of the 16th Men's Handball World Championship on
Wednesday in Egypt's Port Said.
</P>
<P>
China was beaten by Yugoslavia 43-25. Coach of the Chinese
team Li Yingcai attributed the result to the inexperience of the
young players, whose average age stands at 22.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team was formed only a month ago and did not play
even one match, Li told reporters after the match with Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in Group D, European champions Sweden defeated South
Korea 25-20. Sweden, a three-time champions seeking its first
title since 1990, struggled early but slowly took control.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, in Ismailia's Group C, Olympic champions
Croatia beat Kuwait 25-19 and Hungary rolled over Nigeria 34-25.
Five-time African champions Tunisia topped Argentina 23-19 and
Denmark got past Morocco 20-19 in Group A in Cairo; and in Group B,
also in Cairo, Macedonia beat Saudi Arabia 28-21. 
